==English==
Also spelled without the hyphen as '''ballbreaker'''


===Noun===

{{en-noun}}


# ''(vulgar):'' A general use "name-calling" word to emphasize that someone is being punishing or excessively demanding.  
#:''That '''[[SOB]]''' boss of mine expects me to work over the weekend on this project.  What a '''ball-breaker'''!''
# Indicates that a person or object is determined to psychologically '''[[emasculate]]''' a male, not to literally crush his testicles.


===Verb===

'''to ball-break''' (common inflected form '''"breaking my balls"''' )


# Any action which brings significant force, suffering, or pain upon an individual.
#:''Please stop your nagging, this work is hard enough without you '''breaking my balls''' the whole time.''


===Adjective===

'''ball-breaking'''


# Descriptive of anything which portends significant force, suffering, or pain for an individual.
#:''Moving these bags of cement mix will be '''ball-breaking''' work.''
# A word used to exagerate the anticipated consequence that any applicable noun may effect.


